rComments: Didn't know if I liked Rachel at the beginning, however, as time went on she turned out to be a great lecturer. Unfortunately, I found the structure of the course to be rather odd, and the course material itself was quite boring, but it's an easy course.

Prof Kulick's lectures were very organised. Use of TopHat prompted me to complete my readings. She delivered material calmly, yet I remained engaged. I looked forward to lectures because I truly learnt new things each time, and they were just so ... peaceful? :D

Professor Kulick was wonderful. Material of the course was pretty general, but she always used contemporary examples to parallel the protohistoric ones. Couple lectures were a bit duller, but she clearly loves what she teaches and that made it easy to stay engaged. Tests are open ended with lots of room to show your knowledge, readings a bit heavy.
